Defendant Jermaine E.L. Gray in court with Attorney Daniel E Meylink.  Defendant Jermaine E.L. Gray in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be THIRTY-SIX (36) months.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for EIGHTEEN (18) months with credit for FOUR (4) days time served.  Defendant shall serve EIGHTEEN (18) months on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program 
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol; Absolute Sobriety
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Random urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - No physical discipline of his daughter.
 - Defendant to possess NOTHING that looks, shapes or acts like a firearm;
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements by the end of probationary period.  Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  If not paid, will convert to a civil judgment.   

FILED,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
